[Warning: graphic video content] Today is one of the best days of my entire life. 🏳️‍⚧️ Words somewhat fail me because all I can keep repeating over and over again is “oh my gosh I’m so happy” and “I can’t believe this is real.” What a powerful day and moments I’ll never forget for the rest of my life. I feel like my life is truly just beginning and I can’t thank each and every one of you enough. If you’re reading this then you are part of my story and have helped make this happen for me. 🤟

Kelsey, my love, happy two year anniversary baby! I can’t believe how lucky I am to be loved by you and to create this life together. To have a partner as loving and supportive as you is a dream come true. You are the definition of what those words mean. I love you to the moon!

There will be many more “chest reveals” to come as I continue to heal. 🤗 Get ready for all of the shameless shirtless selfies… 😍 I’m absolutely in love with and obsessed with my new chest.

Love,
Luke

node.text:
Last week I was going through my closet to see if there were any clothes I’ve outgrown or don’t bring me joy. 😃 I’ve almost replaced my entire wardrobe in the last 6 months and have held onto a couple of suits that I LOVE so much. My suit jackets have always been a little bit too long in the sleeves and I have always been too lazy to get them tailored. 😅 so I’d just roll the sleeves nbd.

Well, last week when I tried this jacket on I bust out laughing when only one arm was in because I could already feel that I have outgrown it. My back and upper body has grown so much 💪 that even with the jacket on all the way I couldn’t give a hug or raise my arms at all. It was a very surreal, euphoric, and gender affirming feeling to put on old clothes and see and feel the growth that is happening inside and out. One of the perks of keeping old clothes is to be able to track that physical progress! 😍🙌

Swipe for 2 years ago in this jacket 👉

node.text:
When I was first outed (mislabeled) as lesbian and was told that wasn’t acceptable and that my friendships with girls were “inappropriate”, it felt like I was hit over the head. I was so confused about what I was hearing about myself. All of a sudden I was scared that other people could see things about me that I couldn’t see in myself, so I put up walls. Lots of walls. Because I knew deep down there was still more to figure out and I couldn’t let anyone else see it before I could.

When I cut my hair off it was like a got a taste of a little more masculinity and then I wanted more and more. I felt closer to this inner calling that I couldn’t quite put words to yet.

I had to find and create a million different versions of myself to figure out what was real and who I really was. I didn’t know that becoming Luke was a possibility. As soon as I accepted who I was/am, it was like taking my first breath of air. Representation and visibility saves lives. 🏳️‍⚧️

6 months on T 💉 #ftm #transguy #transgender #transisbeautiful

Dressed to the nines @thenineshotel 🔥 6 years together ❤️‍🔥 A lifetime with you isn’t long enough my love.

To my wife:

From the moment we met we faced challenges from life and society, and every time we chose us. You chose me and I chose you. It seems so simple but it’s so powerful to be loved so unconditionally and fearlessly. Our connection was immediate and it felt more like a reunion than a first time meeting. I’ve never known a love like ours before and I cherish what we have more than I could ever put into words.

It’s cliche but these 6 years have been a journey, now more than ever. I am so thankful that you have empowered me to become the man that I am becoming and the way you love me stops me in my tracks. ❤️ I love you more with each passing day.

———

Swipe to the end for a pic of us 6 years ago on our first date at The Weeks concert.

A huge thank you to @thenineshotel for hosting us and celebrating us for our anniversary! They know us so well. Sparking water & a box of @petuniaspiesandpastries 🧁

They made us a reservation for dinner @departurepdx to celebrate. We’ve never had a meal here and were so excited to see so many vegan and GF options! Upon sitting down our waiter said that he’d go get us some mocktails going and if there were any allergies he should know about. I laughed and said “how did you know we want mocktails?!” And he said “there may have been some notes on your reservation 😉.”

😍 @thenineshotel we love y’all

node.text:
Let’s get funking steamy🖕

This shoot will get more and more special as time passes. This was the first time I’ve been in front of a professional lens as Luke, and just 3.5 weeks post op. I felt empowered, handsome, masculine, and so loved.

As a kid and teenager I could never imagine what my future looked like… and now that’s making so much sense. How could I have imagined a life that I marry a woman as incredible and stunning as @kelseystacypearson? How could I imagine that I would one day step into the light, shed those fears and lies and incorrect labels that were placed on me, and live a life as the man I never knew I could be but always wanted to be?

Sometimes dreams are the unthinkable and unimaginable.

I could have never imagined a happy and successful life as a trans man, let alone going through this journey so openly and publicly. But I’m doing it and I’m so grateful for the beautiful and unconditional and fierce love of my wife who has empowered me and encouraged me every step of the way. I’d like to think I could have done this on my own but I really don’t think I could have without her. You’re my hero @kelseystacypearson 💓

Getting to model for @chuyphoto has been an absolute dream come true. He is by far the most genuine, loving, and talented human with a heart of gold. He made us feel so comfortable that we often times got lost in the moment with the music and just basking in our love for each other. I’m just so funking grateful for everything, especially all of you still here reading this long caption haha I have so much love in my heart for each of you 🙏❤️‍🔥

#transisbeautiful 🏳️‍⚧️

Step into my bathroom (and shower 🚿) for my daily grooming routine with all the products that I’m loving right now. Swipe to take a shower with me. 🧔🏻‍♂️Tap through 👉

I’m going to highlight some of what you see:

🪒 I’m not going to be doing my first shave anytime soon but I’m ready for when the time comes with my @leafshave “The Twig” single blade stainless steel razor! We also have “The Leaf” in the shower that can fit 3 blades. Never buy a plastic razor again! A 50 pack of blades costs $12 and you can recycle the used blades. ⚔️

🚿 I had some body acne breakouts for a few weeks after my top surgery and I used @versed Day Maker microcrystal exfoliator in the shower + the Back-Up Plan acne-control mist twice a day and it cleared up so fast.

🥇How I believe I have managed and prevented facial acne throughout taking testosterone for 5+ months: The @drzenovia entire line of products is *chefs kiss* for hormonal acne control. It’s gentle but powerful with results! I 10/10 recommend the Clear Complexion line + the Essentials line.

+ @youthtothepeople Power Mask 🎉 fav mask ever bc *results*

🧼 My favorite natural deodorant that has actually worked day in and day out for me has been @oarsandalps Fresh Ocean Splash.

🧴For my scars, I’m using the Scar Recovery Gel by @skinmedica and CBD salve by @ziggysnaturals (save $ with PEARSON at checkout)

🧔🏻‍♂️Questions about anything?👇
